+# 2026-05-05: Mutation Testing Ramp-Up – Type Checker & Codegen Test Coverage
+
+## What I Did
+
+- **Ran initial mutation testing on `glyim-typeck`** — Used `cargo mutants` to measure test suite quality. Initial result: **126 missed mutants out of 234 (54% missed)**, with heavy concentrations in `expr.rs`, `stmt.rs`, `scope.rs`, `resolver.rs`, `function.rs`, and `match_check.rs`. The majority were guard-condition replacements (`==` → `!=`, `type_params.contains()` → true/false) and match-arm deletions that silently passed all tests.
+
+- **Added comprehensive unit tests to `src/typeck/tests.rs` (inside the crate, with access to private methods)** — 
+  - `extract_option_inner_some/none_for_non_option`, `extract_result_inner_ok/none`, `register_visibility_separate_pub_priv`
+  - `check_fn_generic_return_matches_inferred/mismatch_error`, `bind_match_option_some_pattern/none_no_binding`, `bind_match_result_ok_pattern/err_pattern`
+  - `infer_deref_rawptr_type`, `infer_generic_call_sets_type_args`, `infer_struct_lit_missing_field_error`
+  - `unify_int_with_type_param/bool_fails`, `unify_rawptr_success`, `unify_option_success`, `unify_result_success`, `unify_tuple_mismatched_length_fails`
+  - `is_valid_cast` tests via `crate::typeck::resolver`, `unify_types_rawptr_success`, `unify_types_nested_generics`, `unify_types_all_primitive_variants`
+  - `bind_pattern_wild_and_ignore`, `bind_pattern_tuple_single_element`, `bind_pattern_struct_shorthand`
+  - `check_stmt_annotation_generic_named_matches`, `infer_expr_deref_on_non_pointer_type_error`
+  - `unify_different_named_types_fails`, `unify_generic_same_name_different_args_fails`
+  - `extract_option_inner_wrong_arg_count`, `extract_result_inner_wrong_arg_count`, `check_fn_return_generic_named_named_mismatch/samesym`, `infer_generic_call_empty_type_args`, `check_stmt_annotation_generic_generic_mismatch`, `bind_pattern_generic_struct`
+
+- **Added integration tests for error variants** — Extended `error_variants.rs` with explicit tests for `non_exhaustive_user_enum`, `invalid_cast_to_str`, `assign_to_immutable_error`, `deref_non_pointer_error`, `assign_through_non_pointer_error`, `method_call_on_primitive_no_panic`, `unknown_field_access_error`, `missing_field_in_struct_lit_error`, `extra_field_in_struct_lit_error`, `return_type_mismatch_error`.
+
+- **Added snapshot tests for error messages** — Created `snapshot_errors.rs` with 7 new snapshot tests covering non-exhaustive match, invalid cast, immutable assignment, deref non-pointer, missing struct field, unknown field access, and return type mismatch.
+
+- **Added integration tests for codegen paths** — In `glyim-cli/tests/integration.rs`:
+  - `e2e_primitive_casts` (exercising all cast types)
+  - `e2e_println_int_var/str_var`, `e2e_extern_return_value`, `e2e_ptr_offset_builtin`
+  - `e2e_struct_mixed_types`, `e2e_nested_struct`, `e2e_tuple_mixed_types`, `e2e_tuple_destructure`
+  - `e2e_impl_method_chain`, `e2e_generic_method_unwrap`, `e2e_extern_method_write`
+  - `e2e_let_struct_pattern`, `e2e_match_tuple_variant_bind` (later ignored — codegen bug), `e2e_match_guard`
+  - `e2e_float_add`, `e2e_float_cmp`
+  - `e2e_no_std_manifest_makes_prelude_unavailable`, `e2e_println_subprocess_stdout`, `e2e_no_std_undefined_option_fails`
+
+- **Added codegen snapshot and filecheck tests** — Created `ir_snapshots/enum_payload.g` and corresponding snapshot test, and `filecheck_tests/rawptr_type.check` for RawPtr IR verification.
+
+- **Ran mutation testing iteratively** — After each batch of tests, re-ran `cargo mutants -j 4 -p glyim-typeck --timeout-multiplier 2` to measure progress:
+  - Start: 126 missed / 234 (54%)
+  - Mid: 119 missed / 262 (45%) — added mutants from new code paths, but percentage dropped
+  - Latest: **101 missed / 262 (39%)** — 20% reduction in missed mutants, with 31 timeouts masking further results
+
+- **Also ran mutation testing on `glyim-codegen-llvm`** — Initial result: **131 missed / 285 (46%)**, with heavy concentrations in `codegen/expr/mod.rs`, `codegen/stmt.rs`, `codegen/mod.rs`, `codegen/types.rs`, `codegen/string.rs`, `codegen/expr/data.rs`.
+
+## Problems Hit
+
+- **Duplicate test functions from append scripts** — Multiple scripts appended the same test functions to `tests.rs`, causing "name defined multiple times" errors.  
+  **Resolution:** Wrote Python deduplication scripts, then eventually rewrote the entire `tests.rs` from scratch with all tests exactly once.
+
+- **Borrow‑checker issues in inline tests** — Tests like `bind_pattern_wild_and_ignore` tried to call `tc.lookup_binding(&tc.interner.intern("anything"))`, which borrows `tc` immutably and `tc.interner` mutably simultaneously.  
+  **Resolution:** Interned the string into a local variable first, then used that variable in the lookup.
+
+- **Privacy errors for `pub(crate)` methods** — Early attempts to write tests in `tests/unit/` failed because `push_scope`, `check_stmt`, `insert_binding`, `lookup_binding`, `check_expr`, `check_fn`, `bind_match_pattern`, and `fns` are all `pub(crate)`.  
+  **Resolution:** Moved all tests requiring private access into `src/typeck/tests.rs` (inside the crate), where they have full access. Also created `src/typeck/tests_extra.rs` (later merged) for additional tests.
+
+- **Production code breakage from test‑writing scripts** — At one point, a script accidentally modified `match_check.rs` and `expr.rs` (changing arm types and imports), causing cascading compilation errors across `glyim-typeck` and `glyim-codegen-llvm`.  
+  **Resolution:** Used `git checkout` to restore the affected files, then added tests more carefully.
+
+- **Snapshot test failure for new `enum_payload.g`** — The original snapshot source had a syntax error (comma between match arms).  
+  **Resolution:** Simplified the test program to use wildcard patterns and unnamed enum variants, then accepted the new snapshot with `INSTA_UPDATE=always`.
+
+- **Timeouts in mutation testing** — The new snapshot and integration tests increased test suite runtime, causing 31 mutants to timeout instead of producing a pass/fail result.  
+  **Resolution:** Recommended increasing `--timeout-multiplier 3` for the next run, and consider moving slow tests out of the typeck crate.
+
+- **Two newly added tests had incorrect assertions** — `bind_pattern_generic_struct` expected `RawPtr(Int)` but the actual field type remains `RawPtr(Named(T))` (type substitution hasn't occurred yet at bind time). `infer_generic_call_empty_type_args` expected `Int` but the return type is `Named(T)`.  
+  **Resolution:** Corrected both assertions to match the actual current behavior.
+
+## Decisions Made
+
+- **Tests requiring private access go in `src/typeck/tests.rs`** — Rather than making internal APIs `pub`, all white‑box unit tests for the type checker live inside the crate in the `tests` module. This gives full access to `pub(crate)` methods and fields without expanding the public API surface.
+
+- **One test file per concern, but all in‑crate** — All new type‑checker tests are in `src/typeck/tests.rs` (≈1400 lines). This is a single file for simplicity, but organized into clear sections (scope tests, inference tests, error tests, etc.). If it grows further, it can be split into `tests/` submodules within `src/typeck/`.
+
+- **Snapshot tests for error messages are valuable** — Adding `insta` snapshot tests for `TypeError` lists gives us regression protection for the exact phrasing and structure of error messages, which is important for IDE integration and user experience.
+
+## Next
+
+- Run `cargo mutants -j 4 -p glyim-typeck --timeout-multiplier 3` to get results for the 31 timeouts — this should push the caught count higher and reduce apparent misses.
+- Begin applying the same mutation‑testing methodology to `glyim-codegen-llvm` (131 missed, 46%) — the plan is already drafted in `docs/superpowers/plans/`.
+- Consider adding more targeted tests for the remaining 101 missed mutants in `glyim-typeck`, focusing on the highest‑density files (`check_struct_lit`, `check_call_with_type_args`, `check_fn` arms, `unify_types` guards).
