-# v0.6.0 Phase 2: Rich Errors & Extended Macro API — Type Definitions Implementation Plan
-
-> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (if subagents available) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.
-
-**Scope check:** The v0.6.0 spec's Phase 2 covers: extending `MacroContext` with error reporting methods, multi-span error rendering (done in Phase 1), implementing extended `MacroContext` methods in `glyim-typeck`, `caller_location()`, `read_file()` (sandboxed FS), and dependency tracking. The codebase has NO type checker (`glyim-typeck/src/lib.rs` is `//! TODO`), NO macro expansion pipeline (`glyim-macro-core/src/lib.rs` is `//! TODO`), and NO `MacroContext` trait at all. Implementing any of these methods is impossible. What IS achievable: defining the complete type surface that all future phases depend on — the `MacroContext` trait, all reflection info types, `AttributeArgs` types, `MacroError`, `MacroOutput`, `MacroDefinition`, dependency tracking structures, cache/recorder interfaces. This is a "type design" phase: ~105 tests proving the API surface is coherent, zero runtime behavior.
-
-**Blocked items and what unblocks them:**
-| Item | Blocker |
-|------|---------|
-| Implementing MacroContext methods | Type checker + HIR with structs/enums (v0.3.0+) |
-| Macro expansion calling MacroContext | Macro expansion pipeline (v0.3.0+) |
-| Attribute argument PARSING | v0.5.0 Phase 1 (`#[...]` attrs) + this plan's AttributeArgs types |
-| MacroError used in real error paths | Macro expansion pipeline |
-| Incremental cache WIRING | Macro expansion pipeline + build system |
-| Macro stepper CLI/LSP | Macro expansion pipeline + LSP crate |
-
-**What this plan unblocks:**
-| Future Phase | What This Plan Provides |
-|---|---|
-| Phase 1 remainder (quote→HirBuilder) | `MacroOutput<Expr>` type for macro return values |
-| Phase 3 (attribute arg parsing) | `AttributeArgs`, `AttributeArg`, `AttributeValue` types to parse INTO |
-| Phase 4 (built-in derives) | `MacroDefinition`, `MacroParam`, full `MacroContext` API for derives to call |
-| Phase 5 (composability) | `MacroDefinition.required_traits`, conflict detection types |
-| Phase 6 (incremental) | `MacroExpansionDependencies`, `MacroExpansionCache` trait |
-| Phase 7 (macro debugger) | `MacroExpansionRecorder` trait, `MacroInvocationId` |
-
-**Goal:** Define the complete macro system API surface in `glyim-macro-core`: the `MacroContext<Expr>` trait with all reflection, error, FS, and environment methods; all supporting info types (`TypeInfo`, `FieldInfo`, `VariantInfo`, etc.); `AttributeArgs` structured types; `MacroError`, `MacroOutput`, `MacroDefinition`; and cache/recorder interfaces. All purely additive — zero changes to any existing crate except `glyim-macro-core`.
-
-**Architecture:** `glyim-macro-core` goes from `//! TODO` (1 line) to 8 focused files totaling ~600 LOC with ~105 tests. The crate remains independent of `glyim-hir` and `glyim-parse` — `MacroContext` is generic over `Expr` to avoid coupling. `MacroError` wraps Phase 1's multi-span `Diagnostic`. `AttributeArgs` provides typed accessors (`get_string`, `get_bool`, `get_int`, `get_nested`) but has no parser (that's Phase 3).
-
-**Tech Stack:** Rust, existing crate structure, `glyim-interner::Symbol`, `glyim-diag::{Diagnostic, Span}`
