-# v0.6.0 Phase 4: Built-in Derive Registry and Composability Infrastructure Implementation Plan
-
-> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (if subagents available) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.
-
-**Scope check:** The v0.6.0 spec's Phase 4 covers implementing `@derive(Debug)`, `@derive(Clone)`, `@derive(Eq)`, `@derive(Hash)`, `@derive(Serialize)`, `@derive(Deserialize)`, and `@derive(Default)` as regular Glyim macros in `glyim-std/derive/`. The codebase has NO type checker, NO structs, NO enums, NO impl blocks, NO trait definitions in the parser, NO macro expansion pipeline, and NO `glyim-std` crate. Writing derive macro source code that uses `quote!`, `ctx.get_fields()`, `impl Trait for T { ... }` is impossible — none of that syntax parses. What IS achievable: creating the `glyim-std` crate, a `DeriveRegistry` with metadata for all 7 derives (name, required traits, description), a `ComposabilityChecker` that validates requirement graphs at the metadata level (cycle detection, missing requirements), and registering all 7 built-in derives. The actual derive *bodies* (Glyim source using `quote!`) are deferred until the macro expansion pipeline exists.
-
-**Blocked items and what unblocks them:**
-| Item | Blocker |
-|------|---------|
-| Derive macro source code (`.g` files) | Parser: `impl`, `trait`, `struct`, `enum` syntax + macro expansion pipeline |
-| Derive expansion at compile time | Macro expansion pipeline (v0.3.0+) |
-| Runtime field-level checks (Clone needs Clone on fields) | Type checker (v0.3.0+) |
-| End-to-end `@derive(Debug)` producing `impl Debug` | v0.3.0 structs + v0.4.0 HirItem + v0.6.0-P1 quote expansion |
-
-**What this plan unblocks:**
-| Future Phase | What This Plan Provides |
-|---|---|
-| Phase 5 (composability protocol) | `ComposabilityChecker` metadata-level validation, `DeriveRegistry` for looking up required traits |
-| Phase 1 remainder (quote→HirBuilder) | Registry to look up derive definitions when expanding `@derive(...)` |
-| v0.3.0 type checker | Registry to know which derives exist and what they require |
-| Any derive usage | `DeriveRegistry::get("Debug")` returns metadata, `ComposabilityChecker::check()` validates before expansion |
-
-**Goal:** Create `glyim-std` crate, add `DeriveEntry`/`DeriveRegistry`/`ComposabilityChecker` to `glyim-macro-core`, register all 7 built-in derives with correct metadata (names, required traits, descriptions), and test composability validation (cycle detection, missing requirements, multi-derive ordering).
-
-**Architecture:** `glyim-std` (new tier-3 crate) depends on `glyim-macro-core` and exports `register_builtin_derives()`. `DeriveRegistry` maps `Symbol` → `DeriveEntry`. `ComposabilityChecker` takes a `&DeriveRegistry` and a list of derive names, produces `ComposabilityResult` (ok/warnings/errors). No changes to any existing crate except adding `glyim-std` to the workspace.
-
-**Tech Stack:** Rust, `glyim-interner::Symbol`, existing `glyim-macro-core` types
