-# v0.6.0 Phase 5: Composability Protocol — Dependency Graph, Conflict Types, Expansion Planning Implementation Plan
-
-> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (if subagents available) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.
-
-**Scope check:** The v0.6.0 spec's Phase 5 covers: `requires { }` syntax in macro definitions, requirement checking before expansion, conflict detection for overlapping methods, and ordering guarantees. The codebase has NO macro definition parsing (only `Binding`, `FnDef`, `Stmt`, `Use` items), NO macro expansion pipeline, and NO type checker for impl/method resolution. Writing `requires { }` syntax, running expansion, or checking actual impl blocks is impossible. What IS achievable: a `DependencyGraph` that topologically sorts derive requirements and detects impossible orderings; `ImplConflict`/`ConflictReport` data types for representing method-name collisions; a `MethodConflictChecker` for comparing two sets of method names; and an `ExpansionPlan` that sequences macro expansions in valid order. These are the data structures the expansion pipeline (v0.3.0+) will consume.
-
-**Blocked items and what unblocks them:**
-| Item | Blocker |
-|------|---------|
-| Parsing `requires { Debug }` syntax | Macro definition parsing (v0.3.0+) |
-| Checking actual impl method conflicts | Macro expansion output + type checker (v0.3.0+) |
-| Executing expansion plan | Macro expansion pipeline (v0.3.0+) |
-| `requires` field populated from parsed source | Macro definition parsing |
-
-**What this plan unblocks:**
-| Future Phase | What This Plan Provides |
-|---|---|
-| Macro expansion pipeline (v0.3.0+) | `ExpansionPlan` to sequence expansions; `ConflictReport` to report errors |
-| Phase 6 (incremental) | `DependencyGraph` adjacency for tracking which expansions depend on which |
-| Phase 7 (macro debugger) | `ExpansionPlan` step ordering for stepper display |
-| v0.3.0 type checker | `MethodConflictChecker` to validate after expansion |
-
-**Goal:** Add `DependencyGraph` (topological sort with cycle detection), `ImplConflict`/`ConflictKind`/`ConflictReport` (method collision data types), `MethodConflictChecker` (set intersection for method names), and `ExpansionPlan` (ordered expansion sequence) to `glyim-macro-core`. Integrate `DependencyGraph` with Phase 4's `ComposabilityChecker` for enhanced validation.
-
-**Architecture:** Three new files in `glyim-macro-core`: `dep_graph.rs`, `conflict.rs`, `plan.rs`. `DependencyGraph` uses Kahn's algorithm for topological sort. `MethodConflictChecker` compares `HashSet<Symbol>` method name sets. `ExpansionPlan` wraps a `Vec<Symbol>` with metadata. `ComposabilityChecker::check()` is updated to also run the dependency graph and produce warnings for non-optimal ordering.
-
-**Tech Stack:** Rust, `glyim-interner::Symbol`, existing `glyim-macro-core` types
